==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} *{{m|enm||overheren}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|oferhīeran||to overhear, hear, disobey, disregard, neglect}}, equivalent to {{prefix|over|hear|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|overhoren||to hear, hear about}}, {{cog|de|überhören||to not hear, ignore}}, {{cog|da|overhøre||to overhear}}, {{cog|is|yfirheyra||to hear}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/oʊ.vɚ.hɪɚ/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪə(ɹ)|lang=en}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|overhears|overhearing|overheard}}

# To [[hear]] something that wasn't meant for one's ears.

